com.yantra.yfs.japi

Interface YFSEnvironment

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public interface YFSEnvironment
extends java.io.Serializable
    All API functions expect that you pass a valid environment handle as one of the input parameters. The environment handle is at the core of the extensibility framework. It is the tying thread between different API functions, user exits, and event handlers. It contains information about database transactions, connections, user security, access control, and exception conditions. User exits are passed an environment handle which can be used to invoke the API. If you plan to write independent agents which use an API, you are responsible for creating and releasing the environment handle and managing database transactions.
